Description:
Let Me Entertain You
This gorgeous 4 bedroom, 2 bathroom family home has you covered: With 3 substantial living zones and a huge alfresco space, family life and entertaining have never been so easy! Inject simplicity into daily routines, with schools and shops within walking distance and the waves just down the road. Here you can take the dog down to the beach before work, and still be in the CBD before 9 am.
The kitchen, living, meals and family room opens to the huge alfresco, creating an easy-flowing family hub with enough space for everyone. The practical floorplan allows you to keep an eye on the kids playing in the spacious family hub while you go about your day. The luxe kitchen has a 900mm upright dual-fuel oven with 5-burner gas hob, granite benchtops and an Asko dishwasher.
The alfresco is the perfect for entertaining year-round, with a wood heater and large outdoor kitchen with sink. Relax with a glass of wine and your friends in front of the roaring fire while dinner cooks on the BBQ.
The lounge and stunning master bedroom give adults a peaceful place to put up their feet. The master bedroom features box-windows with views to the landscaped front garden, a large walk-in robe and a chic en suite. The large 2nd, 3rd and 4th bedrooms lie in a wing of their own, with the powder room and stylish bathroom nearby.
Mod cons include evaporative cooling and ducted heating. Hallmarks of a quality build include solid brick construction and energy efficient double-glazed west-facing windows.
The courtyard is perfect for a basketball ring and the lush lawn makes an ideal cricket pitch. Just over the back fence is a stretch of peaceful acreage. The double lock-up garage has a single roller door to the courtyard, offering space to park the boat and there is lots of private street parking for family and friends. Let this incredible home entertain you! View ASAP!

Description:
Live the Dream
This exquisite property boasts a large federation-style home that is full of character and charm and sits high overlooking stunning rural views. It is semi-rural living at its finest all within minutes reach of bay and ocean beaches, golf courses, outstanding wineries & restaurants and just over one hour from Melbourne, 15 minutes to Geelong and 10 minutes to Ocean Grove. ON 1.7 HECTARES IT FEATURES; 4 bedrooms - master with full ensuite, walk in robe and french doors, 3 spacious living rooms, 12ft high ceilings, wide return verandah with large undercover entertaining area, permaculture style veggie garden and orchard, 2 x 31,000 litre tanks plus town supply, circular drive, 6 car garage with bathroom & wood heater, solar panels, easy to maintain park-like gardens, fenced paddock with animal shed and much, much more. Situated just 3 kms out of town this hidden treasure is located in a peaceful haven and will surely impress, so call to arrange an inspection today!

Description:
LIFESTYLE PROPERTY, (APPROX 1670 SQM) LEAFY HAVEN RIGHT IN THE VILLAGE.

All the rooms are extra generous, separate entrance with wide hallway, the lounge room is big enough to dine and relax as well, kitchen combines with informal meals and extra space for more living, double doors open to decking which overlooks matured growth. Three big bedrooms, all with plenty of wardrobe space, central bathroom, 2 toilets and large laundry. No 14 Newcombe has floor space to allow for lots of flexibility and easy to extend. The beauty of this property is live and enjoy as is or adapt easily to work with your lifestyle in the future. Develop STCA. A great home here and so affordable.

Description:
Under Instructions from the mortgagee!
Here lies a sensational opportunity to secure a beautifully presented and extremely low maintenance townhouse in the heart of town. Ideally suited to downsizers & first home buyers.
Features include king size master bedroom with stylish ensuite and large walk in robe. The other two bedrooms are queen size and feature built in robes.
The large lounge is sure to impress and boasts a reverse cycle air conditioner. For added comfort ducted heating features throughout the home.
The gourmet kitchen is fully equipped with ample bench and cupboard space and a large walk in pantry.
The light filled dining area opens up to the north facing courtyard which is perfect for entertaining guests outside or for the green thumb of the house to tend a small garden.
The main bathroom comprises a separate shower and bath. The separate laundry features a large linen press.
A single garage & garden shed completes this fantastic property.
All of this within walking distance to the Drysdale shopping centre, medical clinic and public transport, whilst only a short drive to all the Bellarine peninsula has to offer including stunning beaches, golf courses and wineries.

Description:
Convenient village living in Drysdale
This excellent inner Drysdale downsize is a low maintenance solid brick home with generous light-filled living zones and 2 spacious bedrooms. Set within 300 metres of the Drysdale shopping precinct and close to parks, public transport and the Primary School, this property is all about comfort and convenience.
The home sits on a corner allotment, with one less neighbour than most, and side access from Condy Street. Established low maintenance gardens nestle the North facing front veranda, rear undercover outdoor entertaining area and protected side courtyard, providing a variety of private and inviting spaces to relax outdoors.
Indoors, the lounge is bright with warm northern light and features a built-in bar for enjoyable adult entertaining. Living and lounge are linked via double doors, creating a vast space for family occasions. With doors closed, the separation will please those with different interests. Living flows seamlessly to the rear Alfresco space and garden, and boasts split system AC.
The kitchen/meals zone adjoins the delightful east facing courtyard and offers a refreshing indoor-outdoor atmosphere. Spotless electric cooking appliances and the walk-in pantry will impress.
The master bedroom is a bright and roomy affair, boasting his and her's walk-in robes and semi ensuite access to a fresh 2-way bathroom with bath, shower, vanity and toilet. The 2nd bedroom offers private garden views and built-in robes. The master buds conveniently off the lounge room, whilst bedroom 2 adjoins the living space.
The laundry offers excellent storage, internal garage access and access to the 2nd toilet.
With immaculate presentation, neutral decor and central heating, this convenient Drysdale downsize is ready to enjoy. View without delay!
- Convenient inner Drysdale location on a corner allotment 300 meters from the shops
- Low maintenance 2BR home with 2 spacious living areas and 3 inviting outdoor zones
- Bright north facing lounge room with bar adjoins the master BR with twin WIRs
- Living with split system AC adjoins an undercover Alfresco area and 2nd BR with BIRs
- Spotless kitchen with walk-in pantry and fresh 2-way bathroom with bath and shower
- Storage laden laundry accesses the DLUG and 2nd toilet
Land: 396 sq m approx.

Description:
Circa 1870’s on 1 acre in the centre of town
This charming 1 acre approx. property provides a rare opportunity to own a private rural slice of inner Drysdale, with the option of subdivision (STCA) and the potential for a level of self-sufficiency. Just moments from the town centre this unique home is buffered by spacious grounds and hidden by an established shelter belt.
The original cottage dates from 1873. Subtle period features are carried through into more recent extensions, resulting in a modern and spacious 5 bedroom home with 2 living areas and an open plan kitchen.
Both lounge and living flow through French doors to inviting undercover outdoor areas. The spacious lounge adjoins the façade deck shaded by a specimen Elm. Living merges with a generously proportioned, northwest facing veranda that significantly increases the footprint for entertaining. The country-style kitchen is equipped with all mod cons (including Bosch dishwasher, Savoir-Faire 900mm oven, gas cooktop and range hood) and offers abundant storage.
With privacy in mind, the living zones divide the master and minor bedroom wings. The master bedroom boasts an en suite with shower room with basin and toilet. A family-sized laundry and bathroom, with spa bath and shower, adjoin the minor bedrooms. These rooms are double in size and sit within the original cottage.
Ducting for central gas heating. Split system AC to the central living hub.
Outdoor features are impressive. The detached ‘Hoochie’ is the ultimate man cave boasting concrete floor, wood burner, pizza oven and bar. The 6 bay machinery shed with high clearance sliding door, mezzanine storage, extensive workbench and huge open air parking bay is an important asset to a tradesman. Accesses from Newcombe Street and Portarlington Road aid business and subdivision potential. The rear half of the allotment offers open ground for animals and self-sufficiency (vegetable garden, fruit trees and chicken coop).
You’ll love the space, character and potential of this convenient Drysdale address. View without delay.

Description:
Plenty of Space to Expand
This superb family home has everything that the growing family requires - a spacious interior, plenty of outdoor space, inground pool for those hot summer days and an outdoor entertainment space that is the envy of the neighbourhood.
Situated on almost one acre on the outskirts of Drysdale but within easy access to shopping, public transport and schools the property features a beautiful hedge providing shelter and privacy.
Located on a corner block there is dual street access and ample space for the boat and caravan.
The front of the property is north facing making it light and welcoming. The outdoor centre piece is the solar-heated, salt-chlorinated swimming
pool approximately 9x4.5m which is complimented by extensive decking and an expansive outdoor kitchen and undercover entertaining area.
The interior has an open-plan kitchen/dining area with adjacent family/living. Situated between the kitchen and outdoor area is a huge rumpus/pool room which merges with the decking area. The main bedroom has accompanying ensuite and WIR whilst the minor bedrooms are generous in size. This is a home that has instant living appeal.
Double garage with remote front doors and rear door access has power connected. Floor area approximately 7.5 x 12m.
Rhonda Humpage : 0457 313 609

Description:
“Hazeldene Farm”
Dense and towering shelter-belt trees almost completely conceal this 18 ha – 44 acre approx property from the road, ensuring a secluded retreat for residents. Still in conveniently close proximity to the comprehensive shops and services of Drysdale, it offers a handy place to escape from the daily demands of modern life. Opportunity exists to renovate and/or extend the three bedroom brick dwelling or construction of a new residence could be a very exciting alternative (STCA), taking full advantage of panoramic scenery across Port Phillip bay. Huge dam and paddocks bordered by rural fencing, horse shelters in place plus round yard and 3-bay machinery/hay shed. Only 3km to primary schools and 6km to secondary schools makes for a quick school run. Massive river red gums and pines supply wonderful trees for children to climb. Central to a wealth of nearby beaches, both bay and ocean-side, tourist attractions abound on the Bellarine Peninsula. A terrific place for a weekend retreat or to reside permanently.
A beautiful setting less than 5 minutes to Drysdale, 20 minutes to Geelong, just over an hour to Melbourne (commuters can opt to catch a train from South Geelong station) and around 10 minutes to Ocean Grove beaches.
Insights: 225 Murradoc. Road, DRYSDALE VIC 3222 was last sold in 2015.

Description:
Picture Perfect in Wyndham
This residence is quite, private and unique. Located in central Drysdale in a complex with a true neighbourhood feel, this home is ideal in location and lifestyle. This property is situated within meters of two local medical clinics. It is a short stroll to boutique shopping along the High Street and supermarket outlets Woolworths and Aldi. In addition there are early learning centres and some of the Bellarine's finest educational facilities on your door step.
This home is perfect for a young family, those looking to downsize, or an ideal retirement location. A welcoming community feel greets visitors upon entry to the complex, gorgeous low lying trees frame the home and welcomes one inside. This seven year old home is uplifting and filled with an abundance of natural light. On entering the property, the first living zone has front yard views of the neighbourhood. The living zone has a reverse cycle cooling unit ideal for a comfortable living space all year round. The master bedroom is also to the front of the residence, including a large walk in robe and en suite in white tones, with a shower, vanity and toilet.
Moving further into the property, you are welcomed by a spacious and open plan kitchen, dining and second living zone. The kitchen has ample storage options and is equipped with a near new dishwasher and stainless steel appliances. The free standing bench allows additional work space for the home cook. With back yard views this open plan area seamlessly leads to a rear undercover alfresco area ideal for entertaining friends and family all year round.
The sleeping quarters nestle off the second living area, with two spacious bedrooms with built in robes all serviced by a family bathroom, including a shower, vanity and bath. The laundry is also located in this area of the home, with ample storage and rear access.
This home is serviced by ducted heating throughout, allowing for a comfortable living environment during those cold winter days. Furthermore, a remote controlled double lock up garage with single door rear access leading to the outdoor alfresco area is another design feature of this residence.
With stunning elements throughout and a location second to none, this home is ideal for many. Downsizers, retirees or young families, do not linger this property will not disappoint.
Insights: 29/66 Wyndham Street, DRYSDALE VIC 3222 was last sold in 2015 and 22 other 3 bedroom house in DRYSDALE have recently been sold.

Description:
OVER AN ACRE OF BLISS ON THE BELLARINE & WALK TO THE THE DRYSDALE VILLAGE
Stunning Glenvale custom built home (approx. 5 year old) with quality design and fittings. Wide entrance, the large formal loungeroom could also include formal dining, the second open plan living has generous dining area, gourmet kitchen and plenty more room for the rumpus area, doors open from the living area to a huge wrap round deck with entertaining space undercover as well as more free area for the kids to entertain themselves. Four bedrooms, the main is extra large with ensuite and WIR, others have BIR's, study or fifth bedroom, central bathroom, separate toilet and laundry. Features include evaporative cooling, central gas heating, caesarstone kitchen benches, pantry, double shower, glass splashbacks, dishwasher and so much storage. Double garage with internal access, as well as enormous freestanding 4 vehicle shed and workshop at the rear of the property with toilet facilities and water tank. Northern orientation to the backyard provides great light and makes the living easy here in Landsdale. Walking distance to schools, shops and bike ride or walk The Rail Trail ... the complete living situation.
